<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="236" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1225,2107,611,1012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="236">• Small, arboreal, and mostly insectivorous; gray dorsal fur and white/ivory venter; mouse-like ears with black mask around eyes; and long hairless tail with diagnostic feathered white tip.</paragraph>
